ticularly the influence of antisemitism on the social, religious, and political history of the Canadian Jewish community.  A History of Antisemitism in Canada builds on the foundation of numerous studies on antisemitism in general and on antisemitism in Canada in particular, as well as on the growing body of scholarship in Canadian Jewish studies. It attempts to understand the impact of antisemitism on Canada as a whole and is the first comprehensive account of antisemitism and its effect on the Jewish community of Canada. The book will be valuable to students and scholars not only of Canadian Jewish studies and Canadian ethnic studies but of Canadian history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAntisemitismzCanadaxHistory. 4aHistory: Canadian History. 4aHistory: Jewish Studies. 7aRELIGION / Religious Intolerance, Persecution & Conflict.2bisacsh  aCanada.  aCanadian Jewish community.  aCanadian Jewish studies.  aCanadian history.  aCanadian law.  aCanadian society.  aJews in Canada.  aNorth American Jewish history.  aNorth American Jewish society.  aQuebec Society.  aQuebec history.  aanti-Zionism.  aanti-semitism.  aantisemitism.  aracism in Canada.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703540uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112167540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771121675423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771121675/original  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-127703-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles